sub_title: PhD Candidate | Policy & European Public Health | Applied Anthropology
summary: As a graduate of anthropology, I’ve chosen to specialize in migration and public health. I remain dedicated to academic excellence, in 2016 I presented a paper on Syrian migrants in the Netherlands at a conference in Budapest called: “On the Edge: Genealogies and Futures of Precarity”. In 2017, I had the opportunity to present my thesis research at the 36th Anthropology and Health Conference in Dubrovnik.  I recently finished my studies and am now open for exploring new opportunities!
